HEADWORD: Lions leaf
<hw>Li"on's leaf`</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"⟦ucr⟧nz l⟦emac⟧f`)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A South European plant of the genus
<gen>Leontice</gen> (<spn>Leontice leontopetalum</spn>), the tuberous
roots of which contain so much alkali that they are sometimes used as a
substitute for soap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

